<p class="">I know quite well that the idea that an actual industrial target must be worked out industry by industry has always been resisted. For instance, the export groups have been abolished, and nobody has any idea what their export targets are expected to be. They may reach the Board of Trade, but they never reach industry.<p></p> The next matter on which I wish to touch is that of the school-leaving age. Nothing is more repugnant to my feelings than to have to delay raising the School-leaving age. [<em>Laughter</em>.] The hon. Member is not entitled to question other people's sincerity; he is only entitled to question their sense.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
