        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-46e593f3-6102-41c9-8872-dd8e5e6a505a">
                Mr. Speaker
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-46e593f3-6102-41c9-8872-dd8e5e6a505a" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1947-03-10/debates/f785c2ee-ef4d-402b-a757-3fb657b6fe75/EconomicSituation#contribution-46e593f3-6102-41c9-8872-dd8e5e6a505a">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I have always understood that an hon. Member could quote an article. If an hon. Member has never heard of that paper, I cannot answer for that.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-46e593f3-6102-41c9-8872-dd8e5e6a505a" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
